        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer247590659" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9305544069001357114">Terrifying. <br/><br/>I have read two books that described a nightmare, painted a picture of hell. The second was <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/394535.Blood_Meridian__or_the_Evening_Redness_in_the_West' title='Blood Meridian, or the Evening Redness in the West by Cormac McCarthy' rel='nofollow noopener'>Blood Meridian, or the Evening Redness in the West</a> by Cormac McCarthy and first is Night. <br/><br/>I still think of this book sometimes and shudder and I realize that evil is never too far buried in us. The scene where the line of doomed prisoners splits in two with Mengela conducting, a perverse parody of the last judgment seems ripped from Dante.<br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1509104155i/24290947._SX540_.jpg' width='400' height='190' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/></span>
  <span id="freeText9305544069001357114" style="display:none">Terrifying. <br><br>I have read two books that described a nightmare, painted a picture of hell. The second was <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/394535.Blood_Meridian__or_the_Evening_Redness_in_the_West" title="Blood Meridian, or the Evening Redness in the West by Cormac McCarthy" rel="nofollow noopener">Blood Meridian, or the Evening Redness in the West</a> by Cormac McCarthy and first is Night. <br><br>I still think of this book sometimes and shudder and I realize that evil is never too far buried in us. The scene where the line of doomed prisoners splits in two with Mengela conducting, a perverse parody of the last judgment seems ripped from Dante.<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1509104155i/24290947._SX540_.jpg" width="400" height="190" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
